            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF BUSINESS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;LECTURER IN THE DEPARTMENT OF MARKETING (CONTRACT)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FOB/MKT01/2023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to (i) develop and teach undergraduate, postgraduate and executive courses in Marketing or International Business, (ii) supervise undergraduate and postgraduate research projects, (iii) undertake scholarly research either individually or in collaboration with others, (iv) Participate in professional and community engagement, and (v) perform duties or responsibilities at the Department, Faculty and University levels assigned by the Head of Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have: (i) a doctoral degree in any of the following disciplines: Marketing, International Business, or equivalent domains; (ii) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;show evidence of engagement in research&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(iii) Evidence of research, governance, engagement, and teaching experience (the ability to teach courses related to marketing and\or international business) at University level will be an added advantage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;: In special circumstances, a Master’s degree in Marketing, International Business or equivalent domains with a relevant Bachelor’s degree of at least a 2.1 pass may be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; The University offers a competitive salary and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

