            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF BUSINESS - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF MARKETING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: FB/MKT   1/2022 - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;PART-TIME TEACHING ASSISTANT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt; (1position)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; The successful candidate will be expected to assist with students’ tutorials, marking tutorial exercises, invigilation, practicals, library/internet search, other teaching, learning and research related activities as assigned by the Head of Department and or the assigned lecturers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Candidates should have a minimum of Bachelor’s degree in Marketing/International Business or related qualifications with a minimum of 2(1) or 3.6 GPA.  Preference will be given to those with demonstrable/hands –on knowledge of data analysis using SPSS.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should indicate their availability during the period of 08:00Hrs – 17:00Hrs during which tutorials are normally run. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;The University of Botswana offers competitive part-time rates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

